240
00:20:06,737 --> 00:20:07,868
Then...

241
00:20:08,697 --> 00:20:09,798
What about this?

242
00:20:22,518 --> 00:20:25,187
My gosh. How have you been?

243
00:20:25,288 --> 00:20:27,318
Hi there, Gwang Soon.

244
00:20:27,387 --> 00:20:29,018
I have been waiting for you.

245
00:20:29,088 --> 00:20:31,127
- Wait a minute. - Sure.

246
00:20:31,187 --> 00:20:34,197
I was supposed to meet her at the clothing store in the market.

247
00:20:34,828 --> 00:20:36,927
Has everything been good?

248
00:20:37,268 --> 00:20:40,197
Of course. Nothing ever happens here.

249
00:20:42,137 --> 00:20:44,068
Mi Ryeo has not come yet.

250
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:45,338
What about the child?

251
00:20:46,237 --> 00:20:49,308
There was another problem today, so she is locked up again.

252
00:20:49,608 --> 00:20:52,008
I will bring her later when I come back.

253
00:20:52,078 --> 00:20:53,977
You should get back.

254
00:20:54,048 --> 00:20:56,147
He will get angry again if you are gone for too long.

255
00:20:56,447 --> 00:20:58,118
- See you later. - Sure.

256
00:21:00,558 --> 00:21:02,417
- Follow her. - I shall.

257
00:21:15,637 --> 00:21:16,967
You dropped this.

258
00:21:18,268 --> 00:21:20,108
I see. Thank you.

259
00:21:20,177 --> 00:21:22,377
The secret code is, "I came from Heunhaengi Hill."

260
00:21:22,437 --> 00:21:23,907
I came from Heunhaengi Hill.

261
00:21:27,477 --> 00:21:29,647
I heard there was going to be a feast here,

262
00:21:29,717 --> 00:21:31,917
so I had hoped to make a little spending money.

263
00:21:32,417 --> 00:21:36,088
My gosh, what perfect timing. We are short-staffed right now.

264
00:21:36,157 --> 00:21:39,157
- Let me carry that. - Thank you.

265
00:21:39,427 --> 00:21:41,157
- It is that way. - That way?

266
00:21:41,197 --> 00:21:42,998
- Yes. - What luck.

267
00:21:44,828 --> 00:21:45,967
Let us go as well.

268
00:22:24,108 --> 00:22:25,707
Here you go.

269
00:23:01,008 --> 00:23:02,578
Did you get someone who is skilled?

270
00:23:03,008 --> 00:23:05,647
We hired a carpenter who worked for the palace.

271
00:23:05,707 --> 00:23:07,717
I told him to use...

272
00:23:07,778 --> 00:23:10,217
only the best raw material, so do not worry.

273
00:23:10,848 --> 00:23:12,717
How are we designing the buildings?

274
00:23:12,788 --> 00:23:16,187
He said it would be good to arrange them...

275
00:23:16,258 --> 00:23:19,387
to resemble one of the characters for day, month, or entrance.

276
00:23:19,828 --> 00:23:21,828
Entrance and day seemed too plain,

277
00:23:22,528 --> 00:23:24,427
so I told him to go with month.

278
00:23:24,798 --> 00:23:26,328
I met with other lords,

279
00:23:26,727 --> 00:23:28,697
and the trend of the houses nowadays...

280
00:23:28,937 --> 00:23:31,338
shifted from month to luck.

281
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:33,937
Oh dear. Is that right?

282
00:23:34,637 --> 00:23:38,108
I did not know of the recent trends. I apologize.

283
00:23:38,177 --> 00:23:40,377
My eldest son will live in this house.

284
00:23:40,647 --> 00:23:42,048
Yes, of course.

285
00:23:44,387 --> 00:23:45,947
I like this better.

286
00:23:46,588 --> 00:23:48,487
I hate complicated things.

287
00:23:48,558 --> 00:23:49,887
I prefer this, Dad.

288
00:23:50,157 --> 00:23:52,427
But this will bring you luck.

289
00:23:53,457 --> 00:23:57,167
Furthermore, how many times have I told you to speak properly?

290
00:23:57,467 --> 00:23:59,068
It is "Father", not "Dad".

291
00:23:59,127 --> 00:24:00,437
Yes, Father.

292
00:24:00,498 --> 00:24:01,838
I will go now.

293
00:24:01,998 --> 00:24:04,808
Over here. Carpenter. We need to talk.

294
00:24:05,768 --> 00:24:09,078
You are a minister's son. How long will you act like a child?

295
00:24:09,137 --> 00:24:11,508
Father, do not worry about me.

296
00:24:12,707 --> 00:24:14,447
You should worry about Tae Seo.

297
00:24:14,778 --> 00:24:16,717
Why are you worried about Tae Seo?

298
00:24:17,147 --> 00:24:19,348
The report from the dead secret inspector was submitted.

299
00:24:20,187 --> 00:24:21,318
What did you say?

300
00:24:22,157 --> 00:24:25,387
Tae Seo always seems to leave loose ends.

301
00:24:26,187 --> 00:24:27,998
Everyone is about to find out that you stole the royal offerings...

302
00:24:27,998 --> 00:24:30,568
because he failed to get rid of a mere secret inspector.

303
00:24:30,568 --> 00:24:31,798
Hey, watch your tongue.

304
00:24:32,768 --> 00:24:34,338
Why should you be careful?

305
00:24:34,397 --> 00:24:35,967
You put the King on his throne.

306
00:24:36,768 --> 00:24:39,038
Father. You are the leader of the noblemen...

307
00:24:39,038 --> 00:24:41,437
and a loyal subject who replaced the throne with a different King.

308
00:24:41,437 --> 00:24:43,207
You have nothing to worry about.

309
00:24:45,877 --> 00:24:49,018
We have failed to locate the account book yet.

310
00:24:49,778 --> 00:24:52,618
It is my guess that the King has gotten the Director involved.

311
00:24:52,788 --> 00:24:55,417
It will be troublesome if the Director acquires the evidence.

312
00:24:55,717 --> 00:24:57,528
Being careful can never hurt.

313
00:25:00,358 --> 00:25:04,167
My gosh. It has been a while since I saw your serious face.

314
00:25:07,667 --> 00:25:11,308
Tae Seo must resent us because he is an illegitimate child.

315
00:25:12,268 --> 00:25:14,578
So he used my title as the Chief State Councilor...

316
00:25:14,707 --> 00:25:16,377
to sweet-talk the officials in the countryside...

317
00:25:16,477 --> 00:25:18,477
to increase his assets.

318
00:25:19,848 --> 00:25:23,748
So even if the account book turns up,

319
00:25:23,748 --> 00:25:25,088
we will not be responsible.

320
00:25:26,647 --> 00:25:29,058
It will prove Tae Seo's illegal activity.

321
00:25:31,058 --> 00:25:32,227
What are you talking about?

322
00:25:38,697 --> 00:25:39,768
Hey!

323
00:25:51,108 --> 00:25:54,278
Oh, no. My lord.

324
00:25:55,818 --> 00:25:57,848
I am so sorry.

325
00:26:00,288 --> 00:26:02,387
If you are sorry, work.

326
00:26:03,588 --> 00:26:05,487
You will even risk your life.

327
00:26:06,427 --> 00:26:09,457
Your determination will save Joseon.

328
00:26:13,098 --> 00:26:14,768
How much longer...

329
00:26:15,697 --> 00:26:18,937
will you put up with your lives as farmers, servants, or slaves?

330
00:26:20,268 --> 00:26:21,677
The world must not be run based on ranks!

331
00:26:22,338 --> 00:26:25,048
In our world, we ought to be rewarded for our hard effort.

332
00:26:26,008 --> 00:26:27,318
We must join hands together...

333
00:26:29,778 --> 00:26:31,647
to create that world.

334
00:26:32,417 --> 00:26:33,717
My lord.

335
00:26:34,457 --> 00:26:37,687
Until we achieve our goal, you must make sacrifices.

336
00:26:37,887 --> 00:26:39,487
Yes. I will.

337
00:26:39,858 --> 00:26:40,858
Do you understand?

338
00:26:40,858 --> 00:26:43,127
Yes, I do.

339
00:26:48,098 --> 00:26:49,298
What are you talking about?

340
00:26:49,798 --> 00:26:51,308
Tae Seo wants nothing but your approval.

341
00:26:51,737 --> 00:26:53,808
"Father, just say the word."

342
00:26:53,907 --> 00:26:56,237
"Father, is this enough?"

343
00:26:56,237 --> 00:26:58,808
"Father. Should I fetch you something?"

344
00:27:10,387 --> 00:27:11,528
Gosh.

345
00:27:12,987 --> 00:27:14,328
You really are scary.

346
00:27:14,998 --> 00:27:16,798
Tae Seo works so hard to gain your approval.

347
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:20,127
Gosh. I feel awful for Tae Seo now.

348
00:27:21,568 --> 00:27:25,308
Not all brothers are the same.

349
00:27:26,907 --> 00:27:28,308
Listen, Do Soo.

350
00:27:29,778 --> 00:27:33,348
You must brace yourself.

351
00:27:37,018 --> 00:27:39,647
I will, Father. Please do not worry.

352
00:27:47,088 --> 00:27:48,358
My lord.

353
00:27:49,697 --> 00:27:51,798
Do you have pheasants I could pay as tributes?

354
00:27:52,098 --> 00:27:53,798
Pheasants? Of course.

355
00:27:54,197 --> 00:27:57,937
I just received some pheasants from Suam Valley.

356
00:27:58,167 --> 00:27:59,338
How much?

357
00:28:00,977 --> 00:28:03,877
I need 200 rolls of cotton for a pheasant.

358
00:28:05,207 --> 00:28:06,907
Did you say 200 rolls of cotton?

359
00:28:07,217 --> 00:28:09,048
I could buy a horse with that.

360
00:28:09,748 --> 00:28:13,088
How can a pheasant and a horse cost the same?

361
00:28:13,088 --> 00:28:15,957
Then you can get flogged for not paying the tribute.

362
00:28:16,187 --> 00:28:19,487
If you do not want that, you can sell your children.

363
00:28:19,687 --> 00:28:21,727
My gosh. My lord!

364
00:28:21,858 --> 00:28:23,727
Please give me a cheaper price.

365
00:28:23,727 --> 00:28:25,967
My son has been ill for over a month.

366
00:28:25,967 --> 00:28:27,768
I cannot even afford to buy him any medicine.

367
00:28:27,768 --> 00:28:29,768
Gosh. Come on!

368
00:28:29,768 --> 00:28:31,707
My lord!

369
00:28:31,868 --> 00:28:34,377
What are you looking for? Pheasant?

370
00:28:34,377 --> 00:28:36,207
Can you give me a good one?

371
00:28:36,207 --> 00:28:37,407
Right here.

372
00:28:38,278 --> 00:28:39,647
Look. This looks great.

373
00:28:40,008 --> 00:28:42,018
They gave me a pheasant in exchange for my lunch.

374
00:28:42,278 --> 00:28:44,348
So this is how it made its way to the palace.

375
00:28:45,217 --> 00:28:46,487
How can we call this a country?

376
00:28:46,588 --> 00:28:48,288
Everywhere we go, it reeks of corruption.

377
00:28:48,588 --> 00:28:51,088
Seriously. I should leave Joseon when I can.

378
00:29:12,177 --> 00:29:16,548
Seeing how you are loitering around, you must be craving drinks.

379
00:29:17,118 --> 00:29:20,758
You know, this is the hahyangju only the King gets to drink.

380
00:29:20,917 --> 00:29:23,788
What do you say? Would you like a sip?

381
00:29:23,858 --> 00:29:25,028
Do you want a taste?

382
00:29:26,487 --> 00:29:30,098
No, I am good. We sometimes have this drink too.

383
00:29:30,798 --> 00:29:32,697
Of course I know how rare this liquor is.

384
00:29:36,967 --> 00:29:40,108
Gosh. I guess you hold an important position too.

385
00:29:40,167 --> 00:29:42,608
You must have nine lives to have consumed a royal offering.

386
00:29:42,707 --> 00:29:45,877
If you get caught by the Department of Justice,

387
00:29:45,877 --> 00:29:47,108
you will be as good as dead.

388
00:29:50,118 --> 00:29:52,288
Well, I was born a man.

389
00:29:52,288 --> 00:29:54,887
Instead of worrying about the law and living the life of a fool,

390
00:29:55,088 --> 00:29:59,328
I would rather eat everything I want and die a happy man.

391
00:30:00,627 --> 00:30:01,957
Do you not agree, Chil Guk?

392
00:30:04,697 --> 00:30:05,897
Of course, I do.

393
00:30:07,598 --> 00:30:09,237
Forget about the law.

394
00:30:09,937 --> 00:30:13,338
I, Chil Guk, would rather quit pooping than drinking.

395
00:30:17,008 --> 00:30:18,348
What about you, Pal Soon?

396
00:30:20,877 --> 00:30:22,417
I agree, my dear brother.

397
00:30:22,477 --> 00:30:24,147
Here is the thing about the law.

398
00:30:24,647 --> 00:30:27,487
Breaking it gives us the biggest thrill.

399
00:30:48,578 --> 00:30:51,548
My sister is very shy.

400
00:30:56,348 --> 00:30:57,647
How beautiful.

401
00:31:03,518 --> 00:31:05,927
Do you know that you are adorable?

402
00:31:09,298 --> 00:31:10,397
Come inside.

403
00:31:10,927 --> 00:31:13,798
- Gosh. What are you doing? - Come here.

404
00:31:17,967 --> 00:31:19,368
He said "beautiful", right?

405
00:31:21,538 --> 00:31:22,838
- We should go inside. - Okay.

406
00:31:31,947 --> 00:31:34,618
- My gosh. That is a lot. - Goodness.

407
00:31:34,887 --> 00:31:36,657
- Gosh. - Let us go.

408
00:31:37,627 --> 00:31:38,887
This is crazy.

409
00:31:39,528 --> 00:31:41,528
I am seeing ingredients one would see at the royal kitchen.

410
00:31:41,528 --> 00:31:45,397
Exactly. All these royal offerings should have been served to the King.

411
00:31:45,397 --> 00:31:46,927
(Royal offerings: Goods for kings, magistrates, or the palace)

412
00:31:46,927 --> 00:31:49,038
There is more than food. I see hemp clothes too.

413
00:31:55,437 --> 00:31:56,838
Hey, scoundrels.

414
00:31:57,407 --> 00:31:58,808
Come join me in the backyard.

415
00:31:59,308 --> 00:32:02,377
Sure. I will. It is a great day to be out.

416
00:32:17,568 --> 00:32:20,068
- Mal Jong, you are here. - Hey.

417
00:32:20,528 --> 00:32:23,868
Goodness. I always find you guys here.

418
00:32:25,108 --> 00:32:26,508
Keep playing.

419
00:32:27,167 --> 00:32:28,677
Come here.

420
00:32:30,707 --> 00:32:31,778
Sit down.

421
00:32:32,477 --> 00:32:36,318
Pretty girl, you can sit next to me.

422
00:32:37,518 --> 00:32:38,788
All right. Sit there.

423
00:32:42,558 --> 00:32:43,957
Bring us food!

424
00:32:44,987 --> 00:32:47,858
We just met, so please excuse me for being blunt.

425
00:32:48,727 --> 00:32:51,298
If I may, could I ask who your father is?

426
00:32:53,127 --> 00:32:56,298
I should at least know your family before I accept a free meal.

427
00:32:58,508 --> 00:32:59,637
I do not have a father.

428
00:33:03,278 --> 00:33:04,778
I do not have a father.

429
00:33:14,118 --> 00:33:15,288
Pretty girl.

430
00:33:16,217 --> 00:33:17,357
Have a drink.

431
00:33:38,308 --> 00:33:39,378
This is...

432
00:33:40,708 --> 00:33:42,277
not hahyangju.

433
00:33:45,118 --> 00:33:46,217
What?

434
00:33:47,118 --> 00:33:48,217
What do you mean?

435
00:33:48,357 --> 00:33:51,357
I smell chamomile, not lotus flowers.

436
00:33:55,498 --> 00:33:58,898
I can also taste ginger and a bitter flavor of red peppers.

437
00:34:00,668 --> 00:34:02,467
This is hansan sogokju, is it not?

438
00:34:15,378 --> 00:34:17,418
You really are a man about town.

439
00:34:17,547 --> 00:34:20,748
If you were a secret royal inspector...

440
00:34:20,817 --> 00:34:22,688
who came here to mess things up,

441
00:34:22,757 --> 00:34:25,527
I was going to kill and bury you,

442
00:34:26,058 --> 00:34:28,527
but you know the taste of hansan sogokju?

443
00:34:29,228 --> 00:34:32,868
Are you really a lowly scoundrel, then?

444
00:34:36,098 --> 00:34:38,637
- He tested me on purpose? - Bring more wine!

445
00:34:40,668 --> 00:34:44,248
I noticed on my way in that you have everything.

446
00:34:46,047 --> 00:34:48,777
Do you trade medicinal herbs as well?

447
00:34:50,648 --> 00:34:52,748
We do not deal with medicinal herbs.

448
00:34:53,148 --> 00:34:56,487
The officer in charge of that is too thorough for my liking.

449
00:34:56,887 --> 00:34:58,628
I cannot be bothered to deal with him.

450
00:34:58,788 --> 00:35:00,487
Oh, is that so?

451
00:35:01,797 --> 00:35:04,868
She definitely said it happened while drying aconite.

452
00:35:05,328 --> 00:35:07,168
(Wine)

453
00:35:07,527 --> 00:35:09,467
Where did you get all this wine from?

454
00:35:11,208 --> 00:35:12,237
Do you make it?

455
00:35:12,308 --> 00:35:14,737
What? Oh, yes.

456
00:35:14,907 --> 00:35:17,947
Pretty one, where are you from?

457
00:35:20,078 --> 00:35:21,478
Help me out.

458
00:35:28,587 --> 00:35:32,288
Does it matter where I am from?

459
00:35:32,487 --> 00:35:34,998
The fact that we met today is more important.

460
00:35:37,668 --> 00:35:39,927
Do you know romance?

461
00:35:42,368 --> 00:35:44,197
- So... - Yes?

462
00:35:45,337 --> 00:35:47,208
All this wine.

463
00:35:48,837 --> 00:35:50,708
Where do you make it?

464
00:35:52,878 --> 00:35:55,378
Oh, way over there in Jinsan.

465
00:35:55,518 --> 00:35:59,217
There is a valley called Baekgwiryeong.

466
00:35:59,288 --> 00:36:01,188
That is where we make it.

467
00:36:03,217 --> 00:36:05,887
What do you make other than wine?

468
00:36:07,228 --> 00:36:09,657
We make wine,

469
00:36:09,728 --> 00:36:12,128
weave hemp cloth, make silver...

470
00:36:12,197 --> 00:36:14,337
Silver? Did he say silver?

471
00:36:22,637 --> 00:36:25,148
Thanks to you, I got it done in no time.

472
00:36:25,208 --> 00:36:27,177
You even helped me carry the clothes.

473
00:36:27,248 --> 00:36:29,918
Not at all. Tell me if you need anything else done.

474
00:36:29,978 --> 00:36:32,047
Just pack me a few yukjeon to go.

475
